2. ABOUT:

WisRemote is a python script for controlling wis-streamer from command
line locally or remotely (using SSH).

It includes an option to show a tray icon on gnome-panel to control
the TV stream and to visualize it using a dummy VLC window.

It has been developed for Ubuntu Gutsy 7.10, although it should work
on any other GNU/Linux distribution with not much trouble.



3. DEPENDENCIES:

Needed packages:

-python
-wis-streamer

Optional packages:

-python-gtk2 (for the gnome-panel tray)
-python-paramiko (for controlling wis-streamer remotely using ssh)
-vlc (for watching the TV stream)



